ts to local services, especially in Nuneaton, and believes that residents have been poorly served by Conservative Councillors in Warwickshire – despite being responsible for spending the vast majority of the constantly increased Council Taxes collected in Nuneaton, essential services like education, childcare, care for the elderly, the Fire Service have all been cut to the detriment of Attleborough residents. The Conservatives in Warwick seem happy to blindly follow the bidding of their Government masters.\n\nSteve will be a strong voice for Attleborough and Nuneaton at Shire Hall, Warwick. He will put people before greed."},{"n":"Tess Brookes","p":"Green Party","v":316,"r":4,"e":false,"g":"female","m":"gender_guesser","cf":"high","pid":"16796","img":"https://candidates.democracyclub.org.uk/media/images/people/16796/4d6b3031-031d-4826-b161-30d47faca563.png"}]},{"ward":"Bede","seats":1,"turnout_pct":36.39,"results_url":"https://www.nuneatonandbedworth.gov.uk/election-results","candidates":[{"n":"George Finch","p":"Reform UK","v":1320,"r":1,"e":true,"g":"male","m":"gender_guesser","cf":"high","pid":"118679","img":"https://candidates.democracyclub.org.uk/media/images/people/118679/5da19d1b-fa97-407a-9476-5dd380c37fc3.png"},{"n":"Ivy Winters Wanjiru","p":"Labour Party","v":618,"r":2,"e":false,"g":"female","m":"ons","cf":"high","pid":"128998"},{"n":"Steven Coleman","p":"Conservative and Unionist Party","v":364,"r":3,"e":false,"g":"male","m":"gender_guesser","cf":"high","pid":"128997"}]},{"ward":"Bulkington","seats":1,"turnout_pct":42.78,"results_url":"https://www.nuneatonandbedworth.gov.uk/election-results","candidates":[{"n":"Paul Andrew Smith","p":"Reform UK","v":956,"r":1,"e":true,"g":"male","m":"gender_guesser","cf":"high","pid":"129037"},{"n":"Jack Markham","p":"Conservative and Unionist Party","v":804,"r":2,"e":false,"g":"male","m":"existing","cf":"high","pid":"129035","img":"https://candidates.democracyclub.org.uk/media/images/people/129035/0596b88e-41c8-4644-9364-4004534ba7db.png","stmt":"As the only candidate standing in Bulkington that actually lives in the village, my goals if elected are clear:\n\nSupport community values\n\nEngage frequently with residents\n\nPut Bulkington first!","bd":"2000"},{"n":"Campbell Erskine McKee","p":"Labour Party","v":247,"r":3,"e":false,"g":"male","m":"gender_guesser","cf":"high","pid":"111337"},{"n":"Richard Cope","p":"Green Party","v":244,"r":4,"e":false,"g":"male","m":"existing","cf":"high","pid":"125763"}]},{"ward":"Camp Hill","seats":1,"turnout_pct":28.79,"results_url":"https://www.nuneatonandbedworth.gov.uk/election-results","candidates":[{"n":"Colin Cape","p":"Reform UK","v":740,"r":1,"e":true,"g":"male","m":"existing","cf":"high","pid":"86599"},{"n":"Eric Amaechi","p":"Labour Party","v":370,"r":2,"e":false,"g":"male","m":"existing","cf":"high","pid":"73946","img":"https://candidates.democracyclub.org.uk/media/images/images/73946-2e4a2a53-158f-49c8-87b5-c0e9adcb5b5b.png"},{"n":"Emma Shiers","p":"Green Party","v":285,"r":3,"e":false,"g":"female","m":"gender_guesser","cf":"high","pid":"129053"},{"n":"Romaine Francoise Tabet","p":"Conservative and Unionist Party","v":185,"r":4,"e":false,"g":"female","m":"claude","cf":"high","pid":"111336"},{"n":"Christopher Ryan Gamble","p":"Trade Unionist and Socialist Coalition","v":24,"r":5,"e":false,"g":"male","m":"gender_guesser","cf":"high","pid":"119253"}]},{"ward":"Chilvers Coton","seats":1,"turnout_pct":35.28,"results_url":"https://www.nuneatonandbedworth.gov.uk/election-results","candidates":[{"n":"Tony Venson","p":"Labour Party","v":627,"r":1,"e":true,"g":"male","m":"gender_guesser","cf":"low","pid":"111334"},{"n":"Carolyn Louise Russell","p":"Reform UK","v":609,"r":2,"e":false,"g":"female","m":"gender_guesser","cf":"high","pid":"128812"},{"n":"Jamal Lydon","p":"Green Party","v":367,"r":3,"e":false,"g":"male","m":"claude","cf":"high","pid":"128811"},{"n":"Susan Anne Dalziel","p":"Conservative and Unionist Party","v":152,"r":4,"e":false,"g":"female","m":"existing","cf":"high","pid":"85084","img":"https://candidates.democracyclub.org.uk/media/images/people/85084/db2e6d87-eb7a-487f-a2d2-b671526e1da9.png"},{"n":"Max McGee","p":"Trade Unionist and Socialist Coalition","v":13,"r":5,"e":false,"g":"male","m":"gender_guesser","cf":"high","pid":"81906"}]},{"ward":"Eastboro","seats":1,"turnout_pct":37.19,"results_url":"https://www.nuneatonandbedworth.gov.uk/election-results","candidates":[{"n":"Richard John Brill","p":"Reform UK","v":647,"r":1,"e":true,"g":"male","m":"gender_guesser","cf":"high","pid":"129065"},{"n":"Hari Khela","p":"Conservative and Unionist Party","v":528,"r":2,"e":false,"g":"male","m":"claude","cf":"high","pid":"129068"},{"n":"James Hunter","p":"Green Party","v":364,"r":3,"e":false,"g":"male","m":"gender_guesser","cf":"high","pid":"129066"},{"n":"Sunday Wesley Ajayi","p":"Labour Party","v":225,"r":4,"e":false,"g":"male","m":"claude","cf":"high","pid":"111332"}]},{"ward":"Exhall","seats":1,"turnout_pct":34.94,"results_url":"https://www.nuneatonandbedworth.gov.uk/election-results","candidates":[{"n":"Chris Morris","p":"Reform UK","v":840,"r":1,"e":true,"g":"male","m":"gender_guesser","cf":"low","pid":"126344"},{"n":"Sinead Mulholland","p":"Labour Party","v":377,"r":2,"e":false,"g":"female","m":"claude","cf":"high","pid":"129107"},{"n":"Pete Gilbert","p":"Conservative and Unionist Party","v":357,"r":3,"e":false,"g":"male","m":"claude","cf":"high","pid":"129102"},{"n":"Merle Gering","p":"Green Party","v":314,"r":4,"e":false,"g":"male","m":"gender_guesser","cf":"low","pid":"11808"},{"n":"Eileen Hunter","p":"Trade Unionist and Socialist Coalition","v":39,"r":5,"e":false,"g":"female","m":"existing","cf":"high","pid":"5347","img":"https://candidates.democracyclub.org.uk/media/images/people/5347/d6d94cbb-af49-4593-ab4c-085a829f1315.png"}]},{"ward":"Galley Common","seats":1,"turnout_pct":34.57,"results_url":"https://www.nuneatonandbedworth.gov.uk/election-results","candidates":[{"n":"James Alan Bartlett","p":"Reform UK","v":1159,"r":1,"e":true,"g":"male","m":"gender_guesser","cf":"high","pid":"128972"},{"n":"Richard Baxter-Payne","p":"Conservative and Unionist Party","v":384,"r":2,"e":false,"g":"male","m":"gender_guesser","cf":"high","pid":"81824","img":"https://candidates.democracyclub.org.uk/media/images/images/81824-864f59d4-d80e-4802-bd7f-4e0ad434d641.png"},{"n":"Theo Osemele","p":"Labour Party","v":316,"r":3,"e":false,"g":"male","m":"ons","cf":"high","pid":"128973"},{"n":"Gemma Perry","p":"Green Party","v":312,"r":4,"e":false,"g":"female","m":"gender_guesser","cf":"high","pid":"128974"}]},{"ward":"Heath","seats":1,"turnout_pct":35.3,"results_url":"https://www.nuneatonandbedworth.gov.uk/election-results","candidates":[{"n":"Ali Brassington","p":"Reform UK","v":1121,"r":1,"e":true,"g":"male","m":"claude","cf":"medium","pid":"126345"},{"n":"Julie Anne Jackson","p":"Labour Party","v":425,"r":2,"e":false,"g":"female","m":"existing","cf":"high","pid":"7673","img":"https://candidates.democracyclub.org.uk/media/images/images/7673.png","stmt":"Julie is married with three grown up daughters. She has lived in the Borough nearly all her life. She has been a school governor, actively attends Neighbourhood Watch, resident meetings and Community Forums.  She knows first-hand the concerns and aspirations of local people and has a track record of speaking up for local people on the issues that concern them\r\n\r\nJulie says:\r\n\r\n“Over the last few years, we have seen some significant improvements in Wem Brook like the upgrades in housing, in our parks and beyond. We can though do more to improve our town centre and leisure provision.  We need to aim high and make Nuneaton the town centre we all want and give our young people a place to be proud of.  If re-elected to represent the people of Wem Brook I will continue to work hard for all our residents, be a strong voice for our Borough and make myself available to hear your views and concerns.”\r\n\r\nSome of Julie’s priorities will be to:\r\n\r\n    Demand Warwickshire County Council join Transport for the West Midlands, so we get cheaper and more frequent bus and train journeys.\r\n    Be a strong voice and say no to any attempt to being run from Warwick – we need to keep services local and oppose Conservative attempts at Warwickshire County Council to run all our services\r\n    Continue investment in our Council House stock and build more affordable homes\r\n    Tackle fly tipping and take strong action against those responsible for it\r\n    Invest in our parks, leisure facilities and open spaces","tw":"\"NWBLabour\"","url":"\"http://northwarkslabour.co.uk/\""},{"n":"Sandra Walsh","p":"Conservative and Unionist Party","v":324,"r":3,"e":false,"g":"female","m":"gender_guesser","cf":"high","pid":"111331"},{"n":"Richard Green","p":"Green Party","v":200,"r":4,"e":false,"g":"male","m":"gender_guesser","cf":"high","pid":"129110"},{"n":"Rob Roze","p":"Liberal Democrats","v":169,"r":5,"e":false,"g":"male","m":"gender_guesser","cf":"high","pid":"129111"}]},{"ward":"Milby","seats":1,"turnout_pct":49.64,"results_url":"https://www.nuneatonandbedworth.gov.uk/election-results","candidates":[{"n":"Keith Kondakor","p":"Green Party","v":639,"r":1,"e":true,"g":"male","m":"existing","cf":"high","pid":"5198","img":"https://candidates.democracyclub.org.uk/media/images/people/125761/b0012859-1f05-407b-8e83-b6d33f7f5a2b.png","stmt":"Keith was born in Nuneaton and has lived with his wife, Michele, on St Nicolas Park estate in Nuneaton for 27 years. They are passionate  about protecting and improving our town and have been campaigning on a wide range of local issues for the last two decades.\n\nKeith has been elected three times as Weddington ward borough councillor (2012, 2016 & 2020) and three times as Weddington county councillor (2013,2017 and 2025). In 2024, the Weddington ward was spit in two with the creation of the Milby Ward.  The Borough Council seats for Weddington were won by his wife, Michele and fellow Green, Mike Wright in 2024. Keith always puts the interests of our town ahead of party politics. He is very loud and has been an independent voice on both councils. Before becoming a full time Councillor, he ran his own firm designing broadcast audio electronics and software. In his limited time off he does mountain walking, cycling and, recently, a bit of running.","tw":"\"greennuneaton\"","url":"\"http://www.kondakor.co.uk\"","bd":"1965"},{"n":"Paul Timothy Biggs","p":"Reform UK","v":404,"r":2,"e":false,"g":"male","m":"gender_guesser","cf":"high","pid":"129131"},{"n":"Harvey William Gill","p":"Conservative and Unionist Party","v":304,"r":3,"e":false,"g":"male","m":"gender_guesser","cf":"high","pid":"129134"},{"n":"Michael Fowler","p":"Labour Party","v":80,"r":4,"e":false,"g":"male","m":"gender_guesser","cf":"high","pid":"111304"}]},{"ward":"Poplar","seats":1,"turnout_pct":34.03,"results_url":"https://www.nuneatonandbedworth.gov.uk/election-results","candidates":[{"n":"Stan Carvell","p":"Reform UK","v":746,"r":1,"e":true,"g":"male","m":"claude","cf":"high","pid":"122661"},{"n":"Jas Singh","p":"Conservative and Unionist Party","v":461,"r":2,"e":false,"g":"male","m":"claude","cf":"high","pid":"128982"},{"n":"Krissi Cope","p":"Green Party","v":346,"r":3,"e":false,"g":"female","m":"claude","cf":"high","pid":"86615","img":"https://candidates.democracyclub.org.uk/media/images/people/86615/d93c63dd-c19b-495a-82e3-1cfc664f1367.png","stmt":"Krissi has lived in Bedworth for 18 years. She is married with 3 children, who have all attended local schools, with the eldest now in the local Sixth Form.   Krissi has more than 20 years of retail experience, including 6 years working in the newsagents in town. She now runs her own pet shop business on Bedworth market, which enable her to combine work with her passion for animals.  Being a business owner and trader in Bedworth, Krissi has the both the business skills and people skills that would make her an excellent councillor for Bede ward.   One of her children is disabled and so she has experience of what life is like when you have a child with additional needs  She is a member of the Warwickshire Parent Carer Voice."},{"n":"Adam Bourne","p":"Labour Party","v":326,"r":4,"e":false,"g":"male","m":"gender_guesser","cf":"high","pid":"124566"}]},{"ward":"Slough","seats":1,"turnout_pct":39.64,"results_url":"https://www.nuneatonandbedworth.gov.uk/election-results","candidates":[{"n":"Bobbie Greenwood","p":"Reform UK","v":1063,"r":1,"e":true,"g":"male","m":"gender_guesser","cf":"low","pid":"126346"},{"n":"Martin John Walsh","p":"Conservative and Unionist Party","v":691,"r":2,"e":false,"g":"male","m":"gender_guesser","cf":"high","pid":"74245"},{"n":"Paul Waldron","p":"Labour Party","v":350,"r":3,"e":false,"g":"male","m":"gender_guesser","cf":"high","pid":"111322"},{"n":"Dan Walker","p":"Green Party","v":184,"r":4,"e":false,"g":"male","m":"gender_guesser","cf":"high","pid":"128847"},{"n":"Mark Burdett","p":"Trade Unionist and Socialist Coalition","v":32,"r":5,"e":false,"g":"male","m":"gender_guesser","cf":"high","pid":"111319","img":"https://candidates.democracyclub.org.uk/media/images/people/111319/4b99c511-cc48-4ce3-a169-9e0894196f4d.png"}]},{"ward":"St Mary's","seats":1,"turnout_pct":32.24,"results_url":"https://www.nuneatonandbedworth.gov.uk/election-results","candidates":[{"n":"Nicky King","p":"Labour Party","v":770,"r":1,"e":true,"g":"male","m":"gender_guesser","cf":"high","pid":"111313"},{"n":"Jon-Paul William Clift","p":"Reform UK","v":639,"r":2,"e":false,"g":"male","m":"gender_guesser","cf":"high","pid":"129178"},{"n":"Richard Heathcock","p":"Green Party","v":329,"r":3,"e":false,"g":"male","m":"gender_guesser","cf":"high","pid":"129180"},{"n":"Scott George Moreton Harbison","p":"Conservative and Unionist Party","v":194,"r":4,"e":false,"g":"male","m":"existing","cf":"high","pid":"47225","img":"https://candidates.democracyclub.org.uk/media/images/images/47225-971e788b-8067-4942-9bec-3b46582227bf.png","stmt":"Delighted to have been re-selected to stand for my home ward.  Updates to follow. The election is expected for 6th May 2021. Stay tuned in, don't burn out. ADDENDUM. We won.","bd":"1972"},{"n":"Steven Gee","p":"Trade Unionist and Socialist Coalition","v":32,"r":5,"e":false,"g":"male","m":"gender_guesser","cf":"high","pid":"129179"}]},{"ward":"St Nicolas","seats":1,"turnout_pct":50.25,"results_url":"https://www.nuneatonandbedworth.gov.uk/election-results","candidates":[{"n":"Jake Derrick Groves","p":"Reform UK","v":844,"r":1,"e":true,"g":"male","m":"gender_guesser","cf":"high","pid":"129174"},{"n":"Jamie Marek Hartshorn","p":"Conservative and Unionist Party","v":684,"r":2,"e":false,"g":"male","m":"existing","cf":"high","pid":"84080","img":"https://candidates.democracyclub.org.uk/media/images/people/84080/d518346a-245e-4359-8191-1abf60cad27f.png","tw":"\"jamie4barpool\""},{"n":"Miranda Bishop-Timings","p":"Green Party","v":636,"r":3,"e":false,"g":"female","m":"gender_guesser","cf":"high","pid":"129172"},{"n":"Mustafa Dogal","p":"Labour Party","v":224,"r":4,"e":false,"g":"male","m":"claude","cf":"high","pid":"129173"}]},{"ward":"Stockingford East","seats":1,"turnout_pct":34.41,"results_url":"https://www.nuneatonandbedworth.gov.uk/election-results","candidates":[{"n":"Stuart Finch","p":"Reform UK","v":856,"r":1,"e":true,"g":"male","m":"gender_guesser","cf":"high","pid":"129182"},{"n":"Matthew Carl Smith","p":"Labour Party","v":427,"r":2,"e":false,"g":"male","m":"existing","cf":"high","pid":"111315","img":"https://candidates.democracyclub.org.uk/media/images/people/111315/48feb452-39dd-4a8f-b663-11f5855f4b51.png"},{"n":"Spring Vernon","p":"Green Party","v":292,"r":3,"e":false,"g":"female","m":"claude","cf":"high","pid":"47227"},{"n":"Sebastian Leo Gran","p":"Conservative and Unionist Party","v":261,"r":4,"e":false,"g":"male","m":"gender_guesser","cf":"high","pid":"16887"},{"n":"Daniel Webb","p":"Trade Unionist and Socialist Coalition","v":21,"r":5,"e":false,"g":"male","m":"existing","cf":"high","pid":"111316","img":"https://candidates.democracyclub.org.uk/media/images/people/111316/053d04b8-9e6d-40f7-b48b-a9cc1ea89db5.png"}]},{"ward":"Stockingford West","seats":1,"turnout_pct":32.14,"results_url":"https://www.nuneatonandbedworth.gov.uk/election-results","candidates":[{"n":"Shane Roger Coates-Jarman","p":"Reform UK","v":1086,"r":1,"e":true,"g":"male","m":"gender_guesser","cf":"high","pid":"129168"},{"n":"Kath Price","p":"Labour Party","v":355,"r":2,"e":false,"g":"female","m":"gender_guesser","cf":"high","pid":"73423","stmt":"Kath Price – Your local candidate for Kingswood\n\n“I first moved to Nuneaton 30 years ago and finding a warm and friendly environment, made my home here. I am a Stockingford resident, living on Haunchwood Road. I work as a Social Worker in Adult Social Care in the local area, which gives me an insight into the difficulties that people can encounter in their daily lives.\n\nCommunity is very important to me and during these times of cuts to public services, am happy to support any local community-based initiatives.\n\nI am standing to be your local councillor as I feel I can make a difference.”\n\nKath’s pledges to you:\n\n    To work in partnership with all stakeholders to maximise benefits for local residents     Work to get roads adopted, pathways cleared, rogue trees trimmed, and grot spots dealt with right across Kingswood     Oppose cuts to Stockingford Community Centre which accommodates vital community groups     Hold monthly surgeries to discuss local residents’ concerns."},{"n":"David Fletcher","p":"Green Party","v":236,"r":3,"e":false,"g":"male","m":"gender_guesser","cf":"high","pid":"129169"},{"n":"Abi Olaifa","p":"Conservative and Unionist Party","v":224,"r":4,"e":false,"g":"female","m":"claude","cf":"medium","pid":"129170"}]},{"ward":"Weddington","seats":1,"turnout_pct":42.15,"results_url":"https://www.nuneatonandbedworth.gov.uk/election-results","candidates":[{"n":"Mike Wright","p":"Green Party","v":969,"r":1,"e":true,"g":"male","m":"gender_guesser","cf":"high","pid":"27523","img":"https://candidates.democracyclub.org.uk/media/images/images/27523.png","stmt":"I have lived in Nuneaton for 17 years, working throughout the town and the surrounding area as a self-employed Maths Tutor. I am not a career politician; I am standing for election because I am fed up with what is happening to our town. The town centre - including our once award winning market - is being allowed to fall into a steep decline, whilst ill-judged developments on the fringes are leading to urban sprawl and severe traffic congestion. Mainstream party politics have failed us: only the Greens have the ideas and the commitment necessary to regenerate our area.","url":"\"https://nuneaton.greenparty.org.uk/2018-candidates/mike.html\""},{"n":"John Michael New","p":"Reform UK","v":775,"r":2,"e":false,"g":"male","m":"gender_guesser","cf":"high","pid":"129157"},{"n":"Lilian Pilkington","p":"Conservative and Unionist Party","v":266,"r":3,"e":false,"g":"female","m":"gender_guesser","cf":"high","pid":"111307"},{"n":"Kani Firat Dogal","p":"Labour Party","v":122,"r":4,"e":false,"g":"male","m":"claude","cf":"medium","pid":"129156"},{"n":"Joy Salaja","p":"Liberal Democrats","v":54,"r":5,"e":false,"g":"female","m":"existing","cf":"high","pid":"82867","img":"https://candidates.democracyclub.org.uk/media/images/people/82867/6d90e188-8434-4a50-b856-247360963c15.png","bd":"1990"}]},{"ward":"Whitestone","seats":1,"turnout_pct":48.77,"results_url":"https://www.nuneatonandbedworth.gov.uk/election-results","candidates":[{"n":"Daljit Singh Boughan","p":"Reform UK","v":1052,"r":1,"e":true,"g":"male","m":"claude","cf":"high","pid":"129143"},{"n":"Michael James Green","p":"Conservative and Unionist Party","v":1019,"r":2,"e":false,"g":"male","m":"existing","cf":"high","pid":"86597","img":"https://candidates.democracyclub.org.uk/media/images/people/129150/4fe7e3f8-d8a7-42be-99ee-d3f7ebf062db.png","stmt":"I'm delighted to have been selected as the Conservative candidate for Whitestone. I will work hard for all residents and over the next few weeks will continue my tour of the ward trying to speak to as many residents as possible.\n\nI'm an engineer who has worked at MIRA for over twenty years and I was born and raised in Nuneaton and have lived here with my wife and son except for my time serving the country as a member of HM forces.\n\nI'm a volunteer director at five of our local schools and am treasurer at a local charity that supports the elderly.","li":"\"https://www.linkedin.com/in/michael-green-0122b314b/\"","bd":"1969"},{"n":"Dianne Jean Fowler","p":"Labour Party","v":322,"r":3,"e":false,"g":"female","m":"gender_guesser","cf":"high","pid":"16886"},{"n":"Mick Ludford","p":"Green Party","v":278,"r":4,"e":false,"g":"male","m":"gender_guesser","cf":"high","pid":"129151"}]}]}